# CLAUDE.md

This file is the entrypoint for Claude Code. It tells the agent where to find instructions, what to read first, and what rules are non-negotiable.

## Read Order

Before doing any work, read these files in this order:

1. `$PROJECT_ROOT/AGENTS.md` — Full agent protocol (Memory Bank, git, session continuity)
2. `$PROJECT_ROOT/.cursor/memory/sessionLog.md` — All prior sessions
3. `$PROJECT_ROOT/.cursor/memory/activeContext.md` — Current focus and open questions
4. `$PROJECT_ROOT/.cursor/memory/progress.md` — Milestones and recent completions

## Memory Bank (Summary)

The Memory Bank is a set of 7 markdown files that persist context across sessions. You MUST read them at session start and update them at session end. Full protocol is in `AGENTS.md`.

Files live in: `$PROJECT_ROOT/.cursor/memory/`

## Non-Negotiables

- **No blank slate sessions.** Always read Memory Bank before working.
- **Register every session.** Add an entry to `sessionLog.md` at start, close it at end.
- **Commit frequently.** Every 15-20 minutes of active work. Push at session end.
- **Standard markdown only.** No emoji headers, no unicode bullets. See formatting standards.
- **Never force push.** If push fails, pull with `--no-rebase` then push again.

